g 6. Metre. The metre of the Epistles is the Dactylic Hexameter, in which each verse consists of six feet, and each foot is a dactyl (-*‘*‘), or its equivalent, a spondeo (- -). To this rule the last (sixth) foot is an exception, admitting only of two syllables, of which the last is either long or short.
